LayoutNode.Content: H op in, grab a seat, and say those magical words: 25 dry, please... A nd buckle yourself in for an awesome bite. N umber 25 Dry is a soupless noodle bowl topped with seafood, pork, and others. A ll seems pretty normal until you drench it with the amazing soy sauceconcoction. M y, the flavors are so amazing -- especially when you add the spicy garlic. N oodle dishes here are generally good and better than most places. I also liked the Grilled Pork, which comes moist, juicy, and nicely marinated. N umber 25 Dry, though, is a must-try (remember it's unlisted on the menu). H ave to request "dry" so you don't get it "wet" -- and yes, dry can be better thanwet.

LayoutNode.Content: S ometimes I just don't need a trendy brunch... A nd the long wait and pretentious hipster smug that it comes with. L o and behold Sally's -- serving the basics, but with a touch of love. L ots of comforting diner-esque qualities about this place. Y et, there's enough quirks in the broad menu to appease the playful palette. S ome other bonuses: Not a long wait, lots of seats, and a parking lot! R ange of stuff on the menu from bagels to pancakes, and hashes to benedicts. E asy to find something you'll like, and they're happy to tailor the dishes. S trawberries instead of bananas to top off your Waffle? T hat's not a problem! A nd that Waffle, by the way, is awesome -- perfectly crisp and dense.... U nabashedly topped with Nutella and Walnuts. R eally feel like a kid as you dive into one of those waffles. A nd the Corned Beef Hash is done well... N ot wet like other places, Sally's does the dried, yet moist, style I like. T ry it with Poached Eggs on top!
